</tr>
</table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uerindathsurefoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Erindath Surefoot</A> at: 11/12/01 6:04:33 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usaliciaswiftfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Salicia Swiftfoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>DAOC Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/12/01 6:29:47 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.daocdivine.homestead.com/files/DivineEmblem.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /sticky is just about useless now - /face isn't much bet</span><hr size=1> Well, /stick was put in to help people with slower computers (like me) and slower connections (not me :p) deal with the dancing 2 GHZ + T3 players. <p><CENTER><a href=http://daocdivine.swgo.net/ ><img src=http://www.daocdivine.homestead.com/files/SalDAoCSig.gif border=0 ></a><Center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utandaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>tandaina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/12/01 7:52:11 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /sticky is just about useless now - /face isn't much bet</span><hr size=1> Yeah, my comp lags like crazy.  So I used stick ALOT.  I'd target a mob, even way off.  And hit /stick.  I'd know that even through lag my char would make it to that critter. <br>
<br>
Same with chars in PvP. ECSPECIALLY in PvP where there are lots of folks around stick is about the only way I can navigate well.  It means folks on T1 connections with 2Ghz machines and Gefroce3 cards can't just dance around me in a circle while I lag.  :(   Its not just about useless for me except in VERY close confines.  <p>Silverleaf Goldenthorn<BR>
Warden of Connla
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uillandraazuryne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Illandra Azuryne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/image/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/12/01 7:53:55 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /sticky is just about useless now - /face isn't much bet</span><hr size=1> And the major reason for adding /face was for casters who must be facing in the direction of the enemy for certain spells to work.  Warriors would charge a caster, caster would quickcast, warrior runs through caster, target not in sight/spell fails, warrior smashes caster, caster dead.  Now warrior charges caster, caster /face and quickcast, warrior runs through caster, caster intantly turns and spell goes off on warrior, caster probably still dead, but warrior damaged.<br>
<br>
Illandra Azuryne<br>
Level 32 Druid - Gawaine <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustryhf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stryhf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/12/01 9:17:30 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /sticky is just about useless now - /face isn't much bet</span><hr size=1> The main problem I see with the short range of /follow and /stick is for same realm groups.<br>
<br>
As a bard, I can count the number of times I've left someone behind cause they fall out of /stick range, and hit a tree.<br>
<br>
Don't hate me because I'm too fast...<br>
<br>
They should allow for longer range /stick and /follow for SAME realm folks.<br>
<br>
