</map></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uerindathsurefoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Erindath Surefoot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/13/01 12:07:09 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/bjcabe/emblem.jpg hiegth=125 width=56></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /sticky is just about useless now - /face isn't much bet</span><hr size=1> Yeah i suppose i can see that in huge group conflicts. Didnt see many of them in beta. Defending a keep that we took from Midgard the other day we had about 100 players in the courtyard of one of the keeps and i was getting about 2fps and i would'nt have been able to do much as a tank.<br>
<br>
Stryhf just a suggestion but follow the group, that way no one can fall back behind the spell. I cant stand bards that leave players behind, makes having the song worthless as you have to run back to gather up people you've dropped from the group. Might as well just run normally. <p><table>
<tr>
<td style=filter:glow(color=maroon strength=80)>
<p style="font-size: 13px; font-family: garamond; color: yellow">
<b>Erindath<br>
</b>{Morte Noire}<br>
-=Lvl 35 Lurikeen Ranger=-<br>
~Bedevere~<br>
2605 RPs
</p>
</td>
</tr>
</table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usanterre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Santerre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(11/13/01 8:27:44 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: /sticky is just about useless now - /face isn't much bet</span><hr size=1> In the 50+ person battles such as defending a keep (or more often a gate), as a tank, the best I can do is F1 + stick and hope I am close enough.  This is w/ DSL 1Ghz 512MB GF2 64MB, not exactly a slacker system.  The limited range on /stick has affected me a little bit, but not a ton.<br>
<br>
Without /stick, I don't see how I could ever kill someone that was trying to run from me unless they were already badly hurt.  I suppose I would adjust, but /stick is a big help. <p><BR><br><B><I><img src="http://www.druidmail.com/santerre2.gif">Santerre.</I></B></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessage?topicID=198.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.showMessage?topicID=199.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.emailToFriend?topicID=193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.threadControl?topicID=193.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=193.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm27.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=193.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thedruidsgrovegeneral">General - EQ<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm27">General - DAOC<option value="thedruidsgrovegeneralot">General - OT<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm18">FAQ & Index<option value="thedruidsgrovefrm20">Spoilers<option value="thedruidsgr